==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dinosauria
<hw>Di`no*sau"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ terrible + <?/ lizard.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An
order of extinct mesozoic reptiles, mostly of large size (whence the
name). Notwithstanding their size, they present birdlike characters in
the skeleton, esp. in the pelvis and hind limbs. Some walked on their
three-toed hind feet, thus producing the large ⟦ldquo⟧bird
tracks,⟦rdquo⟧ so-called, of mesozoic sandstones; others were five-toed
and quadrupedal. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Compsognathus</er>, also
<xex>Illustration</xex> of <xex>Dinosaur</xex> in Appendix.</def></p>

<p><ent>Dinotherium</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Dinothere</ent>⟦br⟧
